> DINOBOT had fought better than her.  DINOBOT had seen better than her.  But
> that did not chnage the point that she was better than him.  Having engaged
> wtih superior fighters did not mean that one was superior to their opponent,
> after all.
>
> Each assault he made was disrupted as fi she was reading his spark, even
> when his body was on full blow assault.  Each coutner countered. Each impact
> turned against him as he went at her in a rage.
>
> Her form was more fluid, more graceful than his brutal Metallikido which
> preferred maximum efficiency, and she was in a word of a martial arts master
> 'showing off' as she sent him stumbling away and falling to the ground as he
> hit and rolled, slowly getting up.

<NEW>

HUN-GRR stepped up next to DINOBOT. He didn't have DINOBOT's advanced
training, but he made up for it in sheer brute strength, armor and
firepower, and bucket loads of experience and sheer determination.

Around them RIPPERSNAPPER, BLOT, SINNERTWIN and CUTTHROAT spread out,
weapons drawn and aimed at ANTAGONY.

ANTAGONY for her part had finished spinning through the air and landed
on the ground, for the moment, out of range of the manacles that were
waiting for her. If she was aware of them she gave no sign. Instead
her optics were on her 6 opponents that were before her.

CRYOTEK only smiled as he crossed his arms over his chest and watched
as the battle was about to erupt again.

(TAG)

- Preston
